reviews.text: Empty tables but supposedly all “had reservations” which never turned up so we had to stay seated near the noisy entrance. Multiple times this has happened. As a fairly regular 4S worldwide customer this is pretty disappointing service and policy.
Perfect afternoon tea. Lovely food, scones delicious and a really good amount. Pretty good value too.

Four seasons lounge is always a good a choice if you want to hold a quiet conversation. They have live music but is soft enough for you to hear what your party has to say. The food and drinks are ok, definitely not outstanding. But then again, you can get outstanding food at four season's other food outlets. Their afternoon tea sets are above average but is always booked. So make sure you book ahead of time to avoid disappointments.

result.adr_address: 香港中環金融街8號
result.name: The Lounge

reviews.text:
海景配下午茶！

小編與友人共2人來到四季酒店大堂的The Lounge吃下午茶，坐到了窗邊的位置，要了個2人Set Afternoon Tea($588+10%=$646.8，平均$323.4位，包飲品，可在Tea Signtures和Loose Leaf Tea Selection裡選擇)，那就要了Organic Lychee Green有機荔枝茶和White Tip Darjeeling大吉嶺紅茶(無限添飲)。

首先送來的是一份小食，一口蟹肉沙律tacos(大方量多的蟹肉，不錯)。
Set Afternoon Tea的底層的咸點非常豐富，每人有6件，覺得滿足，小編最喜愛吃咸點了。
中層就是4件scones(有2個是有葡萄乾)，配有3種醬(新鮮的士多啤梨醬、柚子醬和奶油忌廉)，小編的最愛永遠都是奶油忌廉！吃到這裡已經非常地飽了⋯
好了到最後，上層的甜點每人有4件，份量剛剛好，最美味的是朱古力那件吧，還送2個馬卡龍作完美的句號。

即是每人有12件，平均$27件，再加上五星級的服務和舒適的座位，很不錯。
The Lounge 食下午茶，食物多選擇、好味，有現場live band，價錢偏貴 但真的值回票價

Empty tables but supposedly all “had reservations” which never turned up so we had to stay seated near the noisy entrance. Multiple times this has happened. As a fairly regular 4S worldwide customer this is pretty disappointing service and policy.
Perfect afternoon tea. Lovely food, scones delicious and a really good amount. Pretty good value too.

Four seasons lounge is always a good a choice if you want to hold a quiet conversation. They have live music but is soft enough for you to hear what your party has to say. The food and drinks are ok, definitely not outstanding. But then again, you can get outstanding food at four season's other food outlets. Their afternoon tea sets are above average but is always booked. So make sure you book ahead of time to avoid disappointments.

result.adr_address: 8號 Finance St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Four Seasons Hotel Hong Kong

reviews.text:
I really cannot say good enough about the Four Seasons. Everything was absolutely perfect and we had such an incredible time here. 
Especially, this was my proposal trip, and the staff was super supportive and unbelievably accommodating when we needed them a few times. Also the Caprice(the french restaurant) was so good!!! We had dinner there for my proposal to my fiancee. 
Thank you Four Seasons for giving our couple a fantastic experience in HK. We will always remember this trip;)

Outstanding five star hotel with superb views of Hong Kong harbour and six star service.

I've been coming here for years for food, drink and events but never actually stayed at the hotel and yet it has retained a brand new shiny quality feel to it. 

Expect to pay HK$291 inclusive of 10 percent service charge for two coffees. Service is on a level above and beyond the realm of anything experienced in other hotels.

The view on Victoria Bay from the hotel room is very beautiful. The hotel facility is really very high end. The service is professionally customer centred. The location is perfect for anyone who like me works in the central financial district.
I spent over a week in this hotel. I was very pleased with the service and with the location. My room had a wonderful view of the harbor

A lovely hotel with great service and facilities. They make you feel at home and cater to all your needs. The Airport Express bring you direct from Airport to Hong Kong station where the hotel is situated. You are within 15 minutes from many major restaurants and meeting place.
